text=(:table valign=top:)%0a(:cellnr colspan=3 width=380 bgcolor=#004a80 align=center:)%0a!!%25color=#99FFFF%25Ligeia%25%25%0a(:cellnr rowspan=25 width=400 align=center:) %25width=270%25http://i272.photobucket.com/albums/jj190/shokodragoness/ed318baa-f1b9-4bbd-9520-ba488ec7a357_zps4f5c5a03.jpg%0a(:cellnr width=340 colspan=2 align=center:)%0ahttp://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/mta/headers/mta_s.png%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''%25color=#004a80%25Age:''' 27%0a(:cell width=190:) %0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''%25color=#004a80%25Apparent Age:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) Mid-twenties%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''%25color=#004a80%25Height:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) 5' 11"%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''%25color=#004a80%25Build:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) Lithe%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''%25color=#004a80%25Profession:''' %0a(:cell width=190:) Writer %0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''%25color=#004a80%25Public Effects:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) Status (Silver Ladder) 1%0a(Barfly) 1%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''%25color=#004a80%25Order:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) Silver Ladder%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''%25color=#004a80%25Path:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) Mastigos%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''%25color=#004a80%25Cabal:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) None%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''%25color=#004a80%25Player:''' %0a(:cell width=190:) Hemlockandvervain%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''%25color=#004a80%25Theme Music:''' %0a(:cell width=190:) %25newwin%25[[http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E1ZxRs-MUI0 |"George Romero" - The Sprites]]%0a%25newwin%25[[http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eGfw0Qr-A3k | "Paint it Black" - Vanessa Carlton]]%0a(:tableend:)%0ahttp://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/mta/headers/mta_d.png%0a%25rfloat text-align=center margin-top=5px margin-right=15px margin-bottom=5px margin-left=0px width=250 newwin%25http://i272.photobucket.com/albums/jj190/shokodragoness/1c53fd88-6637-4feb-b0d7-372c9a70e262_zps6f020d2e.jpg%0a%25%25%0a%0aHair cropped boyishly-short, Ligeia rarely cuts anything like a polished figure. Her wardrobe is that of a post-punk artiste: hoodies under leather jackets, cigarette-style dark jeans, a shirt with a long-forgotten band logo slapped on the front. Her figure is largely that of the androgyne; any hint of feminine curves obscured at first glance with clothing, her small breasts often obscured by slightly baggy shirts and flattening undergarments. %25%25%0a%0a:%25%25Nimbus%25%25:%0aShadows deepen to an void-like blackness, while whatever color in the area becomes hyper-bright, and each color looks as though it were applied with a brush. Others in the area feel nothing but a creeping sense of dread and claustrophobia, accompanied by the distinct sensation of being hunted. %0a[[%3c%3c]]%0ahttp://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/mta/headers/mta_h.png%0a%25rfloat text-align=center margin-top=5px margin-right=15px margin-bottom=5px margin-left=0px width=350 newwin%25%0aA tried-and-true Savannah native, Ligeia is an alumnus of SCAD. What little she has shared of her banal middle-class suburban upbringing is largely unremarkable, and her deep adoration of horror ''anything'' a clear outgrowth of being largely left up to her own devices in front of the television as a child. %0a%0aSeven months ago she had a drunken shouting match in Consilium with a middling-status member of the Mysterium, and subsequently divorced herself from the Ladder who had been acting as her mentor. Since then, Ligeia has been keeping her head down if she even shows up to an Awakened gathering at all. %0a%0aLigeia is known as Dee Hackett to Sleepers, and is credited as D. Hackett in her column and radio show. %0a%0ahttp://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/mta/headers/mta_rph.png%0a%0a%0a'''Only Make-Believe''' (Silver Ladder/Consilium): Believing in the power of fiction's ability to make the mundane into the alien and vice-versa, Ligeia is a strong proponent of utilizing horror and speculative fiction as a whole to uplift humanity. Where some among the Ladder donate their time and effort to charity, Ligeia instead spends it trying to craft new ways to break the preconceived notions of Sleepers through writing.%0a%0a'''You Got Some Attitude''' (Consilium): Not the most popular among her Order--partially due to her recent blow-up, and partially due to the fact that she has little qualms about telling someone ''exactly'' why they're an idiot, if asked--Ligeia has something of a stained reputation. Many in the Ladder wonder if the weight of the Vox Draconis is one she is meant to bear, for all of her promise. %0a%0a%25lfloat text-align=center margin-top=5px margin-right=15px margin-bottom=5px margin-left=0px width=270%25http://i272.photobucket.com/albums/jj190/shokodragoness/8851b66c-f8ed-445c-840c-4a64cc9ee3d3_zps364b22e8.jpg%0a%0a'''Horrorshow''' (Anyone): An obvious homage to old ''Twilight Zone'' episodes and Lovecraft, ''Night Hollow'' is a late-night radio program that airs bi-weekly on a local Savannah station, with episodes uploaded online for free. Many of the plots are contained within a single half-hour time-frame, and the show itself follows the citizens of a small East Coast fishing town. Occasionally humorous, the show has been met with some manner of a fandom, though the obvious parallels with the success of other, similar shows has caused some speculation as to whether ''Night Hollow'' is riding on their coattails. %0a%0a'''Land of the Dead''' (Anyone): ''Haunted Savannah'' is a new, bi-weekly column that runs in the back pages of one of the numerous newspapers that cater to both tourists and locals. The articles largely focus on the history of the city and its environs, with new haunted locales, interviews, and weird phenomena featured. %0a%0a'''Ghoul's Night Out''' (Anyone): An occasional late-night wanderer of the city, Ligeia can sometimes be found typing away at an all-night diner or scrawling notes in a bar. She imbibes both of a writer's poisons (coffee and alcohol) quite often, and its likely that you might recognize her. %0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0ahttp://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/mta/headers/mta_con.png%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)*[[Giallo]] ''The knife in the dark. The watchful eye. He is always there when you need him most, but believe you need him least.''%0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0ahttp://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/mta/headers/mta_q.png%0aLeave a quote [[Players.LigeiaQuote?action=edit|here]]%0a%0a(:include Players.LigeiaQuote:)%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a(:include CityBook.MageNavigationBar:)
